snippet.title: Equalizer 4 (2026) – First Trailer | Denzel Washington, Jason Statham, Charlize Theron | Concept
snippet.description:
#equalizer #danzelwashington #jasonstatham #charlizetheron 
The legend continues with Equalizer 4 (2026) — a fan-made concept trailer that imagines Denzel Washington returning as Robert McCall, joined by Jason Statham and Charlize Theron in a high-stakes, action-packed continuation of the franchise.

In this reimagined vision, McCall faces his most dangerous mission yet, as powerful enemies emerge from the shadows, forcing him to join forces with unexpected allies. Brutal fight sequences, explosive action, and gripping suspense collide in this imagined sequel that explores justice, vengeance, and sacrifice on a global scale.

With cinematic visuals, intense performances, and a pulse-pounding tone, this concept trailer gives fans a glimpse of what a fourth installment could look like if these powerhouse stars came together on screen.

Disney’s wave of live-action reimaginings may soon reach the shores of Polynesia, as buzz grows around a Moana live-action adaptation starring Dwayne Johnson and Zendaya.

The project, rumored to be titled Moana: Live Action, would reintroduce audiences to the beloved 2016 animated adventure, blending Polynesian mythology with sweeping visuals and music that captured hearts worldwide.

According to early whispers, the live-action retelling will closely follow the original storyline: Moana, the spirited daughter of a chief, sets out across the ocean to restore the heart of Te Fiti and save her people. Along the way, she joins forces with the demigod Maui, leading to a tale of courage, self-discovery, and harmony with nature.

snippet.title: Brassic Series 7 | Official Trailer | Sky
snippet.description:
After six incredible series, the gang are back for one last Brassic. Available 25 September on Sky. 

Series seven will see the gang get an unmissable send-off, as Vinnie and the crew face their biggest challenge yet — clashing with old enemies, confronting long-lost family, and diving headfirst into chaos. It’s a fitting farewell that wraps up their legendary seven-series run in unforgettable Brassic style. 
 
Joe Gilgun (Vinnie) is joined by returning cast Ryan Sampson (Tommo), Michelle Keegan (Erin), Aaron Heffernan (Ashley), Parth Thakerar (JJ), Joanna Higson (Sugar), Steve Evets (Jim) and Bhavna Limbachia (Meena) for another round of escapades, raucous adventure and mischief.

snippet.title: Skepta & Fred again.. - Back 2 Back (London, 2005 - 2025)
snippet.description:
This is a song I’ve always wanted to make
Skep going back 2 back with his young self

I been a fan of skepta for a longgg time
I mean like we all have right?

And yeah I guess this is just like me as a fan making the song I’ve always been fascinated to hear

All these old clips from random parks and backstages and radios where everyone’s freestylin should be in a museum somewhere 
I’ve always loved watching these so tbh the hardest thing here was choosing only like 5 of the 500 golden ones 

Jus the whole sound of grime literally makes me  like patriotic or summin lol
Like the amount of studios in the US I’ve sat in blasting out these beats to people looking at me like what on earth are you playing 😂😂😂

I feel like everyone’s jus hit by the raw energy of this genre 
and I’m honoured to get to do it with goat of the damn thing himself skepta

and of course shoutout to the work of loefah i grew up listening to his shit too

Shot by: DOMAMANIC
Producer: Vincent Benson
Editor: Charlie Hutchins
Colour: Theo Batterham

Roblox is an online platform and game creation system where users can play games, socialize, and create their own games. It provides a user-friendly environment for developers to design games using the Roblox Studio, a powerful game development tool that employs the Lua programming language for scripting. Games on Roblox are hosted on the platform and can range across various genres, including adventure, role-playing, simulations, racing, and more.

Roblox is available on a variety of platforms, making it accessible to a wide audience. It can be played on Windows and macOS through the dedicated desktop apps, as well as on iPhones and iPads via the Roblox app in the App Store. Android users can access it through the Google Play Store, and Xbox One users can enjoy the platform through a dedicated app available in the Microsoft Store. Additionally, the Roblox website allows for account management, game browsing, and launching games.
